            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ELong-term%20success%20is%20achieved%20only%20if%20there%20is%20a%20successor.%20Paul%20knew%20this%20and%20thus%20instructed%20Timothy%20to%20impart%20everything%20he%20had%20learned%20from%20him%20to%20other%20reliable%20people.%20In%202%20Timothy%202%2C%20Paul%20used%20three%20images%20of%20a%20reliable%2C%20faithful%20person.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFirst%2C%20he%20said%20a%20faithful%20person%20is%20like%20a%20soldier%20(2%3A3)%2C%20who%20will%20endure%20hardship%20as%20part%20of%20his%20calling.%20Good%20soldiers%20do%20not%20get%20involved%20in%20things%20that%20distract%20them%20from%20following%20their%20commanders%3B%20no%20matter%20what%2C%20they%20maintain%20their%20focus.%20In%20order%20to%20be%20faithful%20to%20Jesus%2C%20our%20total%20focus%20must%20be%20on%20fighting%20the%20battle%20of%20faith%20with%20Him%2C%20not%20on%20gaining%20worldly%20position.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20second%20image%20of%20a%20faithful%20Christian%20is%20that%20of%20an%20athlete%20(2%3A5).%20An%20athlete%20must%20follow%20all%20the%20rules%20if%20he%20wants%20to%20win%20the%20game.%20To%20break%20the%20rules%20means%20instant%20disqualification.%20The%20image%20of%20the%20athlete%20reflects%20the%20need%20for%20character%20in%20the%20life%20of%20the%20Christian.%20Only%20those%20who%20live%20pure%20lives%20within%20the%20constraints%20of%20God's%20commands%20will%20win%20the%20prize.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20last%20image%20of%20a%20faithful%20Christian%20is%20that%20of%20a%20farmer%20(2%3A6).%20Diligent%2C%20hardworking%20farmers%20are%20models%20of%20patience.%20The%20seeds%20they%20sow%20into%20the%20soil%20must%20gradually%20grow%20into%20crops.%20If%20the%20farmer%20wants%20to%20reap%20a%20harvest%2C%20he%20cannot%20become%20impatient%20and%20dig%20up%20the%20seed%20to%20see%20if%20it%20is%20growing%20yet!%20Similarly%2C%20we%20must%20be%20patient%20with%20our%20growth%20and%20that%20of%20others%20in%20the%20Lord.%20Patiently%20we%20must%20wait%20for%20the%20harvest%20of%20spiritual%20growth.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIf%20you%20find%20a%20focused%2C%20pure%2C%20patient%20servant%20of%20the%20Lord%2C%20invest%20your%20time%20in%20that%20person.%20One%20day%20he%20will%20do%20the%20same%20for%20someone%20else%2C%20and%20your%20life%20will%20have%20counted%20for%20something%20great.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
